{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"After reviewing the issue again I found that there is a deeper \"problem\" in the [ToneMapShader][1]:\r\n\r\n```glsl\r\nfloat fLumAvg = texture2D(luminanceMap, vec2(0.5, 0.5)).r;\r\n...\r\nfloat fLumScaled = (fLumPixel * middleGrey) \/ fLumAvg;\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you can see there is a chance of a division by zero (if the red channel is zero). I could add another EPSILON there or any other reasonable minimal value, but I believe that adding a `minLuminance` (there already is a `maxLuminance`) might be the best solution? But not sure if other caluclations should also take note of this new option (like they do for max). Will update this PR \"soonish\" to also address that issue. But I thought somebody might have some advices here?\r\n\r\n[1]: https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/dev\/examples\/js\/shaders\/ToneMapShader.js#L59\r\n\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2017-04-10T17:42:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11150#issuecomment-293024499","id":293024499,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11150","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5MzAyNDQ5OQ==","updated_at":"2017-04-10T17:42:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/293024499","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mgreter\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mgreter\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercont